  "text": "The user wants to avoid installing Cairo system library. Need to find pure Python alternatives for SVG to PNG conversion. Options could include:\n1. Remove PNG generation entirely (just keep SVG)\n2. Use a different library like svg2png or rasterio \n3. Use headless browser automation (selenium/playwright)\n4. Use Wand (ImageMagick Python bindings) but that also needs system deps\n5. Just generate SVG and let users convert elsewhere\n\nThe simplest solution might be to just remove PNG generation and only output SVG, since the main functionality is sprite generation.",
